Mantle (
Fig. 19C
) very long, twice longer than maximum width, very thin, with mantle organs clearly visible through it. Osphradium and ctenidium long. Osphradium narrow, greenish, 6 times longer than broad. Ctenidium very long and narrow, more than 10 times longer than broad. Hypobranchial gland covered with thick layer of gelatinous mucus. Rectum filled with sediments particles.
